  <Docs>
    <summary>Provides arguments for creating a customized typeface with specific variation, collection, and palette settings.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontArguments` is a ref struct that groups the parameters for creating a customized typeface from an existing <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface>. Use it with <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments)> to produce a typeface with specific variation axis positions, a selected color palette, and optional palette color overrides.

Because this is a `ref struct`, it can only be used on the stack and cannot be stored in fields, arrays, or used across `await` points.

## Examples

```csharp
using var typeface = SKTypeface.FromFile("variable-font.ttf");

var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    VariationDesignPosition = new[] { new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate { Axis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght"), Value = 700 } },
    PaletteIndex = 0,
};

using var boldFace = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format>
    </remarks>
  </Docs>
